Projects

{/* Professional Projects */}

Professional Projects

Brigham Young University - On-Campus Housing System

Collaborated with a team of developers to design, develop, and maintain the On-Campus Housing management system. Developed key components and temporary functionalities using Mendix, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, Angular, and React. Worked primarily on FERPA-protected information and Sensitive Security systems, ensuring compliance and confidentiality.

View Website
{/* Class Projects */}

Class Projects

World Map API Application (JavaScript Fundamentals)

Created a fully functional Angular application using a world map API, featuring an interactive SVG image where users could click on countries to dynamically retrieve and display information about the selected country using an external API.

GitHub Repository

State Government Website (Front-End Web Development)

Developed a multi-page website for a state government office, including detailed information on cities, populations, and income levels. Utilized semantic HTML elements, external CSS, and JavaScript for interactivity, meeting the requirements for accessibility and usability.

GitHub Repository

User Experience Design Prototype

Designed and implemented a rough draft functional prototype for a user experience website project. The prototype demonstrated key user flows and usability, utilizing HTML5 and CSS. The project showcased proficiency in wireframing, mockups, and user testing.

Live Website GitHub Repository

Paradigm Pet Professionals Website Evaluation and Prototype (User Interface Design)

This project involved two major parts. In Part I, I evaluated the “Paradigm Pet Professionals Website,” assessed its SEO strategies, and developed plans for information architecture to meet the needs of various user personas and stakeholders while adhering to accessibility standards. In Part II, I created an interactive desktop prototype that effectively addressed audience and stakeholder needs, showcasing my ability to prototype and communicate design solutions.

Live Prototype GitHub Repository
{/* Relevant Courses in Two Columns */}

Relevant Courses

  • Network and Security Foundations: Covered network classifications, topologies, and security.
  • Data Management Foundations: Introduced SQL, data definition, and manipulation.
  • Data Management Applications: Focused on MySQL, complex queries, and database management.
  • Version Control: Practical use of Git and version control strategies.
  • Hardware and Operating Systems Essentials: Covered computer architecture and OS fundamentals.
  • Data Structures and Algorithms: Focused on dynamic data structures like lists, stacks, queues, and trees.
  • User Interface Design: Explored tools for designing intuitive interfaces, focusing on clarity and usability.
  • Software Engineering: Introduction to software engineering processes, focusing on Agile and Waterfall models.
  • User Experience Design: Covered wireframes, personas, usability testing, and prototype development.
  • Java Fundamentals: Introduction to object-oriented programming in Java.
  • Advanced Data Management: Focused on data extraction and analysis, data marts, and warehouses.
  • Java Frameworks: Covers object-oriented programming and Java frameworks to build complete applications.
